%h3.text-center
  Edit your tag:
%p.text-center
  You can edit your tag only once
.new-tag
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-4
      .col-md-4
        = form_tag rename_tagname_tag_path do
          .input-group
            = text_field_tag 'tag', @tag.tag_name, class: 'form-control'
            %span.input-group-btn
              = submit_tag 'Edit',class: 'btn btn-default'
      .col-md-4
    %hr

.script-container
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-2
      .col-md-8
        .panel-group
          .panel.panel-default
            .panel-body
              %h4.text-center
                Get the Certified Peng button for your content using your TAG - #{@tag.tag_name}:
            .panel-heading{style: 'color: #615e5e; font-size: 15px;'}
              = "<div class='sinatra-like-button'>"
              %br
              = "  <script src='https://www.certifiedpeng.com/like-button/#{@tag.tag_name}' type='text/javascript'></script>"
              %br
              = '</div>'
      .col-md-2
    %hr

.text-container
  .row
    .col-md-3
    .col-md-6
      %b How To:
      %br
      %b Step 1:
      Copy and paste the code snippet above
      %br
      %b Step 2:
      Place the code where you want the Certified Peng button to appear on your web page
      %br
      %b Step 3:
      Upload your web page and watch the clicks count increase
      %br
      %b NB:
      %span
        You can have a Certifed Peng button without adding having a tracking account, but you will not be able to access the
        = link_to 'tracking dashboard', new_user_session_path
        where you can create specific tags for campaigns or specific content
      %br
      %b Advanced - for tag tracking
      %br
      %b Step 4:
      %span
        = link_to 'Register', new_user_registration_path
        for a Certified Peng tracking account:
        = link_to 'click here >', new_user_registration_path
      %br
      %b Step 5:
      %span
        = link_to 'Login', new_user_session_path
        to your account and check your button tag analytics from your dashboard.
        = link_to 'Click here >', dashboard_path
    .col-md-3
